main event: Multiple sightings of a bluish-green saucer-shaped object over Orlando Air Force Base and Winter Park, Florida, on January 31, 1949.
interesting points: The object was compared in size to an automobile wheel and was seen by multiple credible witnesses including air policemen and civilians., It appeared to shimmer with a dull glow and was described as 'a glass with a light behind it.', Witnesses reported speeds between 100 to 150 MPH., The object exhibited circular motion and a steady flight path., The sightings coincided with favorable weather conditions, boasting a clear sky and good visibility.
witness description: Civilian and military personnel including air policemen.
